          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Fan Yong",
          "email": "yong.fan@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2012-06-10 14:40:45.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Fan Yong",
          "email": "yong.fan@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2012-06-10 14:40:45.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-957 lfsck: LFSCK main engine",
        "message": "LU-957 lfsck: LFSCK main engine\n\nImplement the main engine for Lustre online fsck. The kernel\nthread \"lfsck\" scans the system object table by low layer DT\niteration APIs, and will drives registered scrub component(s)\nto check/repair Lustre system.\n\nIt is the controller of the whole LFSCK, and controls the speed,\nincluding the low layer OI scrub (for osd-ldiskfs).\n\nFor urgent mode, like MDT is restored from file-level backup\nagainst ldiskfs, the OI files are invalided. Under such case,\nwe need to rebuild the OI files ASAP, then low layer OI scrub\ninside osd-ldiskfs ignores the main engine speed control, and\nruns with full speed.\n\nSigned-off-by: Fan Yong <yong.fan@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I4d310b63ca3e34c2b7baaacc0f7272d9e8683b8a\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
